               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430918-name-629" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430918-name-629" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430918-name-629" type="surname" value="LINSLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430918-name-629" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE LINSLEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at Brixton. About nine o'clock, on the 12th of Sept., I was standing near Shoreditch church, reading a notice on a board—I felt a tug, I turned round instantly, and caught the prisoner turning from me, and concealing my handkerchief under his coat—I collared him, and gave him in charge—it was found under his coat.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> How far was he from you when you turned? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Five or six feet—I saw my handkerchief in his hand.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> When you found it in his hand, did you seize him? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, and he said a boy gave it him and ran away—I did not see any boy.</p>
